{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KZRpWpqpHEkpF8UskoFyzK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive Codebase Analysis Summary:\n\n1. Project Structure:\n   - Jakarta EE Web Application\n   - Maven-based build system\n   - Open Liberty runtime configuration\n   - Package: jakarta.tutorial.order\n\n2. Build System (Maven):\n   - Java 17\n   - Jakarta EE Web API 10.0.0\n   - H2 Database (version 2.2.224)\n   - Open Liberty Maven Plugin (version 3.10)\n\n3. Key Java Components:\n   - Entities: CustomerOrder, LineItem, Part, Vendor, VendorPart\n   - EJBs: RequestBean, ConfigBean\n   - Web Manager: OrderManager (JSF-based)\n\n4. Configuration:\n   - JPA Persistence Unit with JTA\n   - H2 In-memory Database\n   - Jakarta Faces Servlet\n   - Development Project Stage\n   - Session timeout: 30 minutes\n\n5. Deployment:\n   - WAR packaging\n   - Open Liberty server\n   - HTTP Endpoint on ports 9080 (http), 9443 (https)\n   - Basic authentication realm\n\n6. Web Resources:\n   - XHTML templates for orders and line items\n   - Default CSS stylesheet\n   - Welcome page: order.xhtml\n\nUnique Migration Considerations:\n- Jakarta EE 10 specifics\n- JPA 3.0 configuration\n- EclipseLink logging and DDL generation\n- In-memory H2 database\n- Open Liberty server configuration\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of this codebase for your migration process?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55e73a7c-4fe4-4151-9924-02c4bb9835cf","uuid":"3cf3d312-072f-46da-bcf2-27e552d1c00a"}
